cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a novel regularization method for learning Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and focuses on image classification tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the improvement of neural network performance, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-categories of machine learning and artificial intelligence, such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions theoretical analysis, which may indicate that it belongs to the sub-category of neural and evolutionary computing, such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with modifying convolution filters, which may suggest that it belongs to the sub-category of natural language processing, such as cs.CL (Computation and Language).
